This directory contains the libvorbis source vendored into the
Mozilla tree, along with the moz.build files needed to build it
as part of Firefox.

The upstream git repository is https://gitlab.xiph.org/xiph/vorbis

To view the information about the current version, including the
upstream revision, check the 'origin' section of moz.yaml.

To update the library source, run

  ./mach vendor media/libvorbis/moz.yaml

To update to a specific upstream git tag or commit, use

  ./mach vendor media/libvorbis/moz.yaml -r <commit>

Updates are also scheduled periodically by Updatebot; see the
'updatebot' section of moz.yaml.

A few source files are renamed during vendoring (e.g. lib/block.c
becomes lib/vorbis_block.c) to avoid filename collisions with other
libraries in the Mozilla build. These renames are declared in the
'update-actions' section of moz.yaml and applied automatically by
./mach vendor.
